----------------------------
0.1.2
----------------------------
* sample.conf: change the default useragent to Firefox 1.0.6.
* classes/ChatterGizmo: fix a few bugs related to regaining our primary
    nickname.
* classes/Resolver: use gethostbyname_ex() to resolve hosts if use_ipv6 is
    off (workaround for broken nameservers).
* classes/WrapConn: change nick regain timer from 30 to 15 seconds.
* data/conversions: added a whole bunch of units.
* plugins/Converter: move the conversion tables to data/conversions.
* plugins/Google: add support for 'define: foo', fix parsing of their nasty
    link tracking URLs, fix 'transmangle' crashes, minor cleanups.
* plugins/Misc: add 'tinyurl' command to provide shorter URLs via tinyurl.com
    (suggestion/original patch by 'jinkusu').
* plugins/NetStuff: reload our CCTLD and port lists during rehash.
* plugins/News: remove the Google News parser, they finally have RSS feeds,
    hurrah!
* plugins/SmartyPants: fix incorrect help for search/replace.
* plugins/Video: fix several minor 'imdb' parsing issues.
* plugins/WordStuff: fix several 'urban' parsing issues, add 'bash' command to
    look up quotes on bash.org.

----------------------------
0.1.1             2005-08-07
----------------------------
* classes/ChatterGizmo: fix some issues with rehash not updating the channel
    list properly, remove nasty global rejoins list hack.
* classes/Common: QuoteURL() no longer quotes '=' and '?'.
* classes/HTTPMonster: fix redirection limit not working, fix redirected POST
    requests not using GET on the redirected URL, fix double urlparse for each
    URL which was unquoting spaces somehow.
* classes/WrapConn: make each wrap keep track of it's own channel rejoins,
    fix adding a channel key then rehashing not joining the channel correctly,
    only do join/stoned check if we finished connecting to the server.
* plugins/Google: fix result parsing.
* plugins/Karma: give an error straight away for absurdly long key names.
* plugins/Misc: fix a missing bracket, fix various issues with the 'fedex'
    command page parsing.
* plugins/MoneyMangler: fix 'asx' page parsing, rename all of the page parsing
    methods to __Parse_Foo.
* plugins/Quotes: add a new 'allow_public_addquote' option, guess what it
    does!
* plugins/TorrentScraper: add a new 'ttl' page type, simplify 'bnbt' page
    parsing, don't retry broken torrents (404, etc) for a while, don't start
    the RSS feed generation timer if rss_interval is 0, fix some more quoted
    entity nastiness.
* plugins/Video: disable 'tvtome' command, since Cnet bought them out and it
    now sucks.
* plugins/WordStuff: fix 'acronym' page parsing, fix 'urban' page parsing.

----------------------------
0.1.0             2005-05-25
----------------------------
* Initial release.
